{"title_page": "Mohd Puad Zarkashi", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Malay name|Puad|Zarkashi}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berbahagia]] [[Malay titles#Datuk|Datuk]]\n| name = Mohd Puad Zarkashi\n| honorific-suffix = {{small|[[Order of Meritorious Service#Commander|PJN]] [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|DSAP]]}}\n| image =\n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1957|07|07|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Johor]], [[Federation of Malaya]]\n| residence =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| constituency_MP1 = [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]]\n| parliament1 = Malaysian\n| term_start1       = 2008\n| term_end1         = 2013\n| majority1         = 12,968 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])\n| predecessor1 = Junaidy Abdul Wahab ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]]\u2014[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor1 = [[Mohd Idris Jusi]] ([[Parti Keadilan Rakyat|PKR]]\u2014[[Pakatan Rakyat|PR]])\n| office = [[Ministry of Education (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Education II]]\n| term_start = 10 April 2009 \t\n| term_end = 15 May 2013\n| constituency = [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]]\n| primeminister = [[Najib Razak]]\n| minister = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| predecessor = [[Razali Ismail]]\n| monarch = [[Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|Mizan Zainal Abidin]]<br />[[Abdul Halim of Kedah|Abdul Halim]]\n| successor = [[Mary Yap Kain Ching]]\n| party = [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO)\n| otherparty = [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN)\n| occupation = [[Politician]]\n| relations =\n| spouse = Rubiah Leman\n| children =\n| alma_mater = [[University of Hull]]\n| website = {{url|http://puadzarkashii.blogspot.com/}}\n| footnotes =\n}}\n'''Mohd Puad Zarkashi''' (born 7 July 1957) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO), a major component party in the [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN) coalition. He was the [[Dewan Rakyat|Member of Parliament]] for the [[Batu Pahat]] constituency in the state of [[Johor]] from 2008 to 2013.\n\nPuad is of [[Banjar people|Banjar]] descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kalsel.antaranews.com/berita/21554/keturunan-banjar-di-malaysia-jadi-melayu-baru |title=Keturunan Banjar Di Malaysia Jadi Melayu Baru - ANTARA News Kalimantan Selatan - ANTARA News Kalimantan Selatan - Berita Terkini Kalimantan Selatan |format= |work= |accessdate=2015-10-09}}</ref> He holds a [[Doctor of Philosophy]] conferred by the [[University of Hull]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/index.php?id=142&act=division&cat=BA&rid=83|title=Y.B. Dr. Mohd Puad Zarkashi|publisher=Ministry of Education|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nPuad was elected at the [[2008 Malaysian general election|2008 election]] for the seat previously held by UMNO's Junaidy Abdul Wahab.<ref name=\"election results\">{{Cite web\n  | last =\n  | first =\n  | authorlink =\n  | author2 =\n  | title = Malaysia Decides 2008\n  | work = [[The Star (Malaysia)]]\n  | publisher = Star Publications (Malaysia)\n  | date =\n  | url = http://thestar.com.my/election/\n  | format =\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 28 January 2010}} Percentage figures are calculated based on total turnout. Includes results from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref> He had previously been a [[Dewan Negara|Senator]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/7/18/parliament/18333422&sec=parliament|title=Senator shares ideas on how to revive glory of Malaysian football|date=18 July 2007|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|publisher=Star Publications (Malaysia)|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref> Puad served one term in Parliament, after being defeated in the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]] by [[Mohd Idris Jusi]] of the opposition [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] (PKR). Despite his defeat, he was re-elected to UMNO's 25-member Supreme Council later in the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2013/10/20/umno-polls-final-results/|title=Umno polls: Results for VP and supreme council|date=20 October 2013|work=The Star|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> Puad was dropped as candidate by UMNO in the [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]].\n\nIn April 2008, Puad called for the resignation of then Prime Minister [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]] after UMNO's performance in the 2008 election.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v5/newsindex.php?id=324914|title=Johor Umno Will Not Stop Divisions From Holding EGM, Says Ghani|date=5 April 2008|work=[[Bernama]]|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nWhen [[Najib Razak]] replaced Abdullah as Prime Minister in April 2009, Puad was appointed a Deputy Education Minister.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v5/newsgeneral.php?id=402979|title=Najib Announces 28-member Cabinet|date=9 April 2009|work=[[Bernama]]|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/?id=142&lang=my|title=Anggota Pentadbiran|publisher=Ministry of Education|language=Malay|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Puad stated his belief that homosexuals could be identified through various means including the use of \"V-Neck and sleeveless clothing\" as well as a person's personal preference for \"tight and light-colored clothing\". He stated that these characteristics were \"symptoms\" which would allow parents to spot whether or not their son may be a homosexual, supporting the need to discipline them into turning straight \"like it's a disease which can be cured\" \u2013 a stance that is also endorsed by Malaysia's Education Ministry because they believe that this could actually affect one's ability to learn.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/208795|title=Guidelines to identify gay and lesbian symptoms published|date=13 September 2012|work=[[MalaysiaKini]]|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref>\n\nPuad was appointed the [[Special Affairs Department]] (JASA) director-general in March 2015 but he quit on 25 April 2018 in protest for not being picked as a BN candidate for the [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/nation/2018/04/25/puad-zarkashi-quits-as-jasa-chief/|title=Puad Zarkashi quits as Jasa chief|date=25 April 2018 |work=[[Free Malaysia Today]]|accessdate=25 April 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sinarharian.com.my/nasional/mohd-puad-lepas-jawatan-kp-jasa-kerana-tak-tercalon-1.826455|title=Mohd Puad lepas jawatan KP Jasa kerana tak tercalon - Nasional|author=MUHAMMAD SHAMSUL ABD GHANI |publisher=[[Sinar Harian]]|date=25 April 2018 |language=Malay|work=[[Sinar Harian]]|accessdate=25 April 2018 }}</ref><ref name=bubar>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=23 May 2018 |title=4 Agensi Dibubarkan Kerajaan Bawah Pimpinan Tun Mahathir. Apa Fungsi Mereka Sebelum Ni? |url=https://soscili.my/4-agensi-dibubarkan-kerajaan-bawah-pimpinan-tun-mahathir-apa-fungsi-mereka-sebelum-ni/ |newspaper=CILISOS |location= |language=Malay|access-date=23 May 2018 }}</ref> JASA was somehow disbanded months later by the new [[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) government after the downfall of the BN in the 2018 election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/government-public-policy/2018/05/372323/spad-jasa-jkkkp-dissolved|title=SPAD, JASA, JKKKP dissolved|date=23 May 2018 |work= NSTP Team |publisher=[[New Strait Times]]|accessdate=25 May 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Laporan: 800 hilang kerja bila JASA tutup |date=20 September 2018 |url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/443858 |author=|work=[[Malaysiakini]] |language=Malay |accessdate=21 September 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]''': P150 [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]], Johor<ref name=\"election results\"/>\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|Government\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opposition\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Mohd Puad Zarkashi'''}} ([[UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |32,461\n|62.42%\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Muhamad Abdullah ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |19,757\n|37.58%\n|54,103\n|12,968\n|77.21%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|Mohd Puad Zarkashi}} ([[UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |36,935\n|48.99%\n|{{Party shading/Keadilan}} |\n|'''[[Mohd Idris Jusi]]''' ([[Parti Keadilan Rakyat|PKR]])\n|align=\"right\" |38,667\n|51.01%\n|77,202\n|1,524\n|87.46%\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* {{Flag|Malaysia}} :\n** [[File:MY Darjah Jasa Negara - Order of Meritorious Service - PJN.svg|50px]] Commander of the [[Order of Meritorious Service#Commander|Order of Meritorious Service]] (PJN) - '''Datuk''' (2014)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2014/06/07/list-of-recipients--federal-awards-and-medals-2014/|date=7 June 2014|accessdate=14 October 2018|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|title=List of recipients of Federal awards and medals 2014}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Pahang}} :\n** [[File:MY-PAH Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang - Knight Companion - DSAP.svg|50px]] Knight Companion of the [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang]] (DSAP) - '''Dato'''' (2009)\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puad Zarkashi, Puad}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Negara]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Hull]]\n[[Category:United Malays National Organisation politicians]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:People from Johor]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of Meritorious Service]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Banjar descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Malay name|Puad|Zarkashi}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berbahagia]] [[Malay titles#Datuk|Datuk]]\n| name = Mohd Puad Zarkashi\n| honorific-suffix = {{small|[[Order of Meritorious Service#Commander|PJN]] [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|DSAP]]}}\n| image =\n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1957|07|07|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Johor]], [[Federation of Malaya]]\n| residence =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| constituency_MP1 = [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]]\n| parliament1 = Malaysian\n| term_start1       = 2008\n| term_end1         = 2013\n| majority1         = 12,968 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])\n| predecessor1 = Junaidy Abdul Wahab ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]]\u2014[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor1 = [[Mohd Idris Jusi]] ([[Parti Keadilan Rakyat|PKR]]\u2014[[Pakatan Rakyat|PR]])\n| office = [[Ministry of Education (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Education II]]\n| term_start = 10 April 2009 \t\n| term_end = 15 May 2013\n| constituency = [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]]\n| primeminister = [[Najib Razak]]\n| minister = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| predecessor = [[Razali Ismail]]\n| monarch = [[Mizan Zainal Abidin of Terengganu|Mizan Zainal Abidin]]<br />[[Abdul Halim of Kedah|Abdul Halim]]\n| successor = [[Mary Yap Kain Ching]]\n| party = [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO)\n| otherparty = [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN)\n| occupation = [[Politician]]\n| relations =\n| spouse = Rubiah Leman\n| children =\n| alma_mater = [[University of Hull]]\n| website = {{url|http://puadzarkashii.blogspot.com/}}\n| footnotes =\n}}\n'''Mohd Puad Zarkashi''' (born 7 July 1957) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO), a major component party in the [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN) coalition. He was the [[Dewan Rakyat|Member of Parliament]] for the [[Batu Pahat]] constituency in the state of [[Johor]] from 2008 to 2013.\n\nPuad is of [[Banjar people|Banjar]] descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kalsel.antaranews.com/berita/21554/keturunan-banjar-di-malaysia-jadi-melayu-baru |title=Keturunan Banjar Di Malaysia Jadi Melayu Baru - ANTARA News Kalimantan Selatan - ANTARA News Kalimantan Selatan - Berita Terkini Kalimantan Selatan |format= |work= |accessdate=2015-10-09}}</ref> He holds a [[Doctor of Philosophy]] conferred by the [[University of Hull]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/index.php?id=142&act=division&cat=BA&rid=83|title=Y.B. Dr. Mohd Puad Zarkashi|publisher=Ministry of Education|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nPuad was elected at the [[2008 Malaysian general election|2008 election]] for the seat previously held by UMNO's Junaidy Abdul Wahab.<ref name=\"election results\">{{Cite web\n  | last =\n  | first =\n  | authorlink =\n  | author2 =\n  | title = Malaysia Decides 2008\n  | work = [[The Star (Malaysia)]]\n  | publisher = Star Publications (Malaysia)\n  | date =\n  | url = http://thestar.com.my/election/\n  | format =\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 28 January 2010}} Percentage figures are calculated based on total turnout. Includes results from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref> He had previously been a [[Dewan Negara|Senator]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/7/18/parliament/18333422&sec=parliament|title=Senator shares ideas on how to revive glory of Malaysian football|date=18 July 2007|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|publisher=Star Publications (Malaysia)|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref> Puad served one term in Parliament, after being defeated in the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]] by [[Mohd Idris Jusi]] of the opposition [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] (PKR). Despite his defeat, he was re-elected to UMNO's 25-member Supreme Council later in the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2013/10/20/umno-polls-final-results/|title=Umno polls: Results for VP and supreme council|date=20 October 2013|work=The Star|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> Puad was dropped as candidate by UMNO in the [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]].\n\nIn April 2008, Puad called for the resignation of then Prime Minister [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]] after UMNO's performance in the 2008 election.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v5/newsindex.php?id=324914|title=Johor Umno Will Not Stop Divisions From Holding EGM, Says Ghani|date=5 April 2008|work=[[Bernama]]|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nWhen [[Najib Razak]] replaced Abdullah as Prime Minister in April 2009, Puad was appointed a Deputy Education Minister.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v5/newsgeneral.php?id=402979|title=Najib Announces 28-member Cabinet|date=9 April 2009|work=[[Bernama]]|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moe.gov.my/?id=142&lang=my|title=Anggota Pentadbiran|publisher=Ministry of Education|language=Malay|accessdate=29 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Puad stated his belief that homosexuals could be identified through various means including the use of \"V-Neck and sleeveless clothing\" as well as a person's personal preference for \"tight and light-colored clothing\". He stated that these characteristics were \"symptoms\" which would allow parents to spot whether or not their son may be a homosexual, supporting the need to discipline them into turning straight \"like it's a disease which can be cured\" \u2013 a stance that is also endorsed by Malaysia's Education Ministry because they believe that this could actually affect one's ability to learn.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.malaysiakini.com/news/208795|title=Guidelines to identify gay and lesbian symptoms published|date=13 September 2012|work=[[MalaysiaKini]]|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref>\n\nPuad was appointed the [[Special Affairs Department]] (JASA) director-general in March 2015 but he quit on 25 April 2018 in protest for not being picked as a BN candidate for the [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/nation/2018/04/25/puad-zarkashi-quits-as-jasa-chief/|title=Puad Zarkashi quits as Jasa chief|date=25 April 2018 |work=[[Free Malaysia Today]]|accessdate=25 April 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sinarharian.com.my/nasional/mohd-puad-lepas-jawatan-kp-jasa-kerana-tak-tercalon-1.826455|title=Mohd Puad lepas jawatan KP Jasa kerana tak tercalon - Nasional|author=MUHAMMAD SHAMSUL ABD GHANI |publisher=[[Sinar Harian]]|date=25 April 2018 |language=Malay|work=[[Sinar Harian]]|accessdate=25 April 2018 }}</ref><ref name=bubar>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=23 May 2018 |title=4 Agensi Dibubarkan Kerajaan Bawah Pimpinan Tun Mahathir. Apa Fungsi Mereka Sebelum Ni? |url=https://soscili.my/4-agensi-dibubarkan-kerajaan-bawah-pimpinan-tun-mahathir-apa-fungsi-mereka-sebelum-ni/ |newspaper=CILISOS |location= |language=Malay|access-date=23 May 2018 }}</ref> JASA was somehow disbanded months later by the new [[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) government after the downfall of the BN in the 2018 election.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/government-public-policy/2018/05/372323/spad-jasa-jkkkp-dissolved|title=SPAD, JASA, JKKKP dissolved|date=23 May 2018 |work= NSTP Team |publisher=[[New Strait Times]]|accessdate=25 May 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Laporan: 800 hilang kerja bila JASA tutup |date=20 September 2018 |url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/443858 |author=|work=[[Malaysiakini]] |language=Malay |accessdate=21 September 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]''': P150 [[Batu Pahat (federal constituency)|Batu Pahat]], Johor<ref name=\"election results\"/>\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|Government\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opposition\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Mohd Puad Zarkashi'''}} ([[UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |32,461\n|62.42%\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Muhamad Abdullah ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |19,757\n|37.58%\n|54,103\n|12,968\n|77.21%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|{{nowrap|Mohd Puad Zarkashi}} ([[UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |36,935\n|48.99%\n|{{Party shading/Keadilan}} |\n|'''[[Mohd Idris Jusi]]''' ([[Parti Keadilan Rakyat|PKR]])\n|align=\"right\" |38,667\n|51.01%\n|77,202\n|1,524\n|87.46%\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* {{Flag|Malaysia}} :\n** [[File:MY Darjah Jasa Negara - Order of Meritorious Service - PJN.svg|50px]] Commander of the [[Order of Meritorious Service#Commander|Order of Meritorious Service]] (PJN) - '''Datuk''' (2014)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2014/06/07/list-of-recipients--federal-awards-and-medals-2014/|date=7 June 2014|accessdate=14 October 2018|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|title=List of recipients of Federal awards and medals 2014}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Pahang}} :\n** [[File:MY-PAH Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang - Knight Companion - DSAP.svg|50px]] Knight Companion of the [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Pahang|Order of Sultan Ahmad Shah of Pahang]] (DSAP) - '''Dato'''' (2009)\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puad Zarkashi, Puad}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Negara]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Hull]]\n[[Category:United Malays National Organisation politicians]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:People from Johor]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Order of Meritorious Service]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Banjar descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian people]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:duplicate categorization; already in subcat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohd_Puad_Zarkashi"}
{"title_page": "Yeshivas Ner Yisroel of Toronto", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n|name              = Yeshivas Ner Yisroel\n|native_name       = \u05d9\u05e9\u05d9\u05d1\u05ea \u05e0\u05e8 \u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\n|motto             = Ki Ner Mitzva V'Torah Ohr\n\u05db\u05d9 \u05e0\u05e8 \u05de\u05e6\u05d5\u05d4 \u05d5\u05ea\u05d5\u05e8\u05d4 \u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\n|streetaddress     = 250 Bathurst Glen\n|city              = [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]]\n|province          = [[Ontario]]\n|country           = {{flag|Canada}}\n|established       = 1959<ref name=GovRec>{{cite web\n        |title=Ner Israel Yeshiva College Act, 2000\n        |url=https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/pr00005 |website=ontario.ca |date=June 23, 2000}}</ref>\n|head              = [[Uri Mayerfeld|Uri S. Mayerfeld]] and Meyer D. Greenberger\n|accreditation     = Full Ontario Diploma\n|head_name         = \n|head_name2        = \n|head2             = \n|r_head_label      = \n|r_head            = \n|affiliation       = [[Ultra-Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox]] \n|free_label        = \n|free              = \n}}\n'''Yeshivas Ner Yisroel of Toronto (Ner Israel Yeshiva College)''' ({{lang-he|\u05e0\u05e8 \u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc}}) is a [[Haredi Judaism|Haredi]] [[yeshiva]] (Jewish educational institution) in [[Vaughan]], [[Ontario]], Canada with government recognition of its degree-granting programs.<ref name=GovRec/>\n\n==Programs==\nThe yeshiva has been granted restricted degree-granting authority by the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]],<ref>http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/source/private/english/2000/elaws_src_private_pr00005_e.htm An Act respecting Ner Israel Yeshiva College</ref> to grant degrees in the field of religious studies and research in higher Jewish learning at the Bachelors, and Masters levels. In addition, the College offers University Diplomas and Certificates.<ref>http://www.cicic.ca/en/postsec.aspx?sortcode=2.20.24.26&id_postsec=257 Ner Israel Yeshiva College Directory of Universities, Colleges and Schools in Canada</ref>\n\nThe current [[Rosh yeshiva|Roshei Yeshivos]] (headmasters) are Rabbi [[Uri Mayerfeld]]<ref name=rose/> and Rabbi Meyer D. Greenberger. The [[Mashgiach Ruchani]] of the Beis Midrash program is Rabbi Nechemia Rockove. The Menahel of the High School is Rabbi Moshe Englander. The Mashgiach of the High School is Rabbi Yeruchum F. Kravetz.\n\nThe current [[Rabbi|Rebbeim]] (religious studies faculty) are, for grade nine, Rabbi Enkin and Rabbi Spinrad. For grade ten are Rabbi Garfunkel and Rabbi Greenberg. For grade eleven are, Rabbi Rockove and Rabbi Fiveashevitz. For grade twelve are, Rabbi Nulman and Rabbi Green. \n\nThe head of the general studies department is Jory Vernon.\n\n==History==\nThe yeshiva was established by Sholom Gold in 1959<ref name=GovRec/> as a branch of [[Yeshivas Ner Yisroel]] in [[Baltimore]] (NIRC).\nMeyer Lebovic was also involved.<ref>{{cite web  |author=Binyamin Rose|url=http://rabbizweig.com/Mishpacha.pdf    |title=Early Riser}}</ref> The yeshiva opened in September of that year with 12 students.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our History  |url=http://www.neryisroel.info/our-history}}</ref> The yeshiva has grown to approximately 130 students since then.\n\nIn 1964 [[Yaakov Weinberg]] came from NIRC<ref>{{cite web |title=Shmuel Yaakov Weinberg (1923 - 1999)\n|url=https://www.geni.com/people/Rav-Yaakov-Weinberg/6000000002852798886\n|quote=In 1964, Weinberg went to the Yeshivas Ner Yisroel of Toronto}}</ref> and assumed the post of [[Rosh Yeshiva]] until 1971. The yeshiva was next headed by Naftali Friedler. The mantle of Rosh Yeshiva was then assumed by Gavriel Ginsburg in 1988.<ref name=rose>{{cite magazine|last=Rose|first=Binyamin|author-link=|date=Dec 23, 2015|title=Inside the Cruz Campaign|url= |magazine=[[Mishpacha]]|issue=590|page=34}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ontario Student Assistance Program]]\n*[[Higher education in Ontario]]\n*[[List of yeshivas]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{Ont post-secondary|d}}\n{{OrthodoxJudaism}}\n\n{{coord|43|50|21.5|N|79|27|52|W|display=title}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://neryisroel.info Official website]\n\n[[Category:High schools in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Orthodox yeshivas in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1959]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Ontario]]\n\n\n{{Yeshiva-stub}}\n{{Ontario-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n|name              = Yeshivas Ner Yisroel\n|native_name       = \u05d9\u05e9\u05d9\u05d1\u05ea \u05e0\u05e8 \u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc\n|motto             = Ki Ner Mitzva V'Torah Ohr\n\u05db\u05d9 \u05e0\u05e8 \u05de\u05e6\u05d5\u05d4 \u05d5\u05ea\u05d5\u05e8\u05d4 \u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\n|streetaddress     = 250 Bathurst Glen\n|city              = [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]]\n|province          = [[Ontario]]\n|country           = {{flag|Canada}}\n|established       = 1959<ref name=GovRec>{{cite web\n        |title=Ner Israel Yeshiva College Act, 2000\n        |url=https://www.ontario.ca/laws/statute/pr00005 |website=ontario.ca |date=June 23, 2000}}</ref>\n|head              = Uri S. Mayerfeld and Meyer D. Greenberger\n|accreditation     = Full Ontario Diploma\n|head_name         = \n|head_name2        = \n|head2             = \n|r_head_label      = \n|r_head            = \n|affiliation       = [[Ultra-Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox]] \n|free_label        = \n|free              = \n}}\n'''Yeshivas Ner Yisroel of Toronto (Ner Israel Yeshiva College)''' ({{lang-he|\u05e0\u05e8 \u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc}}) is a [[Haredi Judaism|Haredi]] [[yeshiva]] (Jewish educational institution) in [[Vaughan]], [[Ontario]], Canada with government recognition of its degree-granting programs.<ref name=GovRec/>\n\n==Programs==\nThe yeshiva has been granted restricted degree-granting authority by the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]],<ref>http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/source/private/english/2000/elaws_src_private_pr00005_e.htm An Act respecting Ner Israel Yeshiva College</ref> to grant degrees in the field of religious studies and research in higher Jewish learning at the Bachelors, and Masters levels. In addition, the College offers University Diplomas and Certificates.<ref>http://www.cicic.ca/en/postsec.aspx?sortcode=2.20.24.26&id_postsec=257 Ner Israel Yeshiva College Directory of Universities, Colleges and Schools in Canada</ref>\n\nThe current [[Rosh yeshiva|Roshei Yeshivos]] (headmasters) are Rabbi Uri Mayerfeld<ref name=rose/> and Rabbi Meyer D. Greenberger. The [[Mashgiach Ruchani]] of the Beis Midrash program is Rabbi Nechemia Rockove. The Menahel of the High School is Rabbi Moshe Englander. The Mashgiach of the High School is Rabbi Yeruchum F. Kravetz.\n\nThe current [[Rabbi|Rebbeim]] (religious studies faculty) are, for grade nine, Rabbi Enkin and Rabbi Spinrad. For grade ten are Rabbi Garfunkel and Rabbi Greenberg. For grade eleven are, Rabbi Rockove and Rabbi Fiveashevitz. For grade twelve are, Rabbi Nulman and Rabbi Green. \n\nThe head of the general studies department is Jory Vernon.\n\n==History==\nThe yeshiva was established by Sholom Gold in 1959<ref name=GovRec/> as a branch of [[Yeshivas Ner Yisroel]] in [[Baltimore]] (NIRC).\nMeyer Lebovic was also involved.<ref>{{cite web  |author=Binyamin Rose|url=http://rabbizweig.com/Mishpacha.pdf    |title=Early Riser}}</ref> The yeshiva opened in September of that year with 12 students.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our History  |url=http://www.neryisroel.info/our-history}}</ref> The yeshiva has grown to approximately 130 students since then.\n\nIn 1964 [[Yaakov Weinberg]] came from NIRC<ref>{{cite web |title=Shmuel Yaakov Weinberg (1923 - 1999)\n|url=https://www.geni.com/people/Rav-Yaakov-Weinberg/6000000002852798886\n|quote=In 1964, Weinberg went to the Yeshivas Ner Yisroel of Toronto}}</ref> and assumed the post of [[Rosh Yeshiva]] until 1971. The yeshiva was next headed by Naftali Friedler. The mantle of Rosh Yeshiva was then assumed by Gavriel Ginsburg in 1988.<ref name=rose>{{cite magazine|last=Rose|first=Binyamin|author-link=|date=Dec 23, 2015|title=Inside the Cruz Campaign|url= |magazine=[[Mishpacha]]|issue=590|page=34}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ontario Student Assistance Program]]\n*[[Higher education in Ontario]]\n*[[List of yeshivas]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{Ont post-secondary|d}}\n{{OrthodoxJudaism}}\n\n{{coord|43|50|21.5|N|79|27|52|W|display=title}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://neryisroel.info Official website]\n\n[[Category:High schools in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Orthodox yeshivas in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1959]]\n[[Category:1959 establishments in Ontario]]\n\n\n{{Yeshiva-stub}}\n{{Ontario-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Edms1485", "label": "safe", "comment": "link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yeshivas_Ner_Yisroel_of_Toronto"}
{"title_page": "Tony Pua", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=May 2019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Pan (surname)|Pua (\u6f58)]]}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Other salutations|Tuan]]\n| name          = Tony Pua\n| native_name   = {{nobold|\u6f58\u4fed\u4f1f}}\n| native_name_lang = zh-my\n| honorific-suffix = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image         = 20110414TonyPuaThursday.jpg\n| caption       = Tony Pua giving a speech in a public rally\n| constituency_MP = {{pseat|Damansara}} (earlier {{pseat|Petaling Jaya Utara}})\n| parliament    = Malaysian\n| term_start    = 8 March 2008\n| term_end      =\n| majority      = 19,972 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])<br />44,672 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])<br />106,903 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n| predecessor   = [[Chew Mei Fun]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]]\u2013[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor     =\n| birth_name    = Tony Pua Kiam Wee\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1972|08|01|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Batu Pahat]], [[Johor]], [[Malaysia]]<ref>{{in lang|zh}} [http://www.sinchew-i.com/sciWWW/node/1501?tid=19 \u5f9e\u653f\u7406\u5ff5\u7c21\u55ae\u8e0f\u5be6\u2027\u6f58\u5109\u5049\u8981\u5e6b\u52a9\u66f4\u591a\u4eba], 1 June 2008, Sinchew Jitpoh</ref>\n| party         = [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP)\n| otherparty    = [[Pakatan Rakyat]] (PR) (2008-2015)<br />[[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) (2015-present)\n| occupation    = [[Politician]], [[investor]]\n| alma_mater    = [[Keble College, Oxford]]\n| website       = {{URL|tonypua.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Tony Pua Kiam Wee''' ({{zh|t=\u6f58\u5109\u5049|s=\u6f58\u4fed\u4f1f|p=P\u0101n Ji\u01cenw\u011bi}}; born 1 August 1972) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP) currently serving as three-term [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] representing [[Damansara (federal constituency)|Damansara]] and Political Secretary to the [[Minister of Finance (Malaysia)|Minister of Finance]] of [[Malaysia]], [[Lim Guan Eng]]. Pua is the former Malaysian CEO of Cyber Village Sdn Bhd, a SESDAQ ([[Singapore Exchange|SGX]] second board)-listed company. In early 2007, he disposed of all his interests in the company and tendered his resignation to join the DAP in 2008.\n\nPua graduated from [[Keble College, Oxford]] with a degree in [[Philosophy, Politics and Economics]] under a scholarship from the [[British American Tobacco|MTC Foundation]] in 1994. Before that, he received Asean and Shaw Foundation scholarships to pursue his O- and A-Levels in [[Raffles Institution]] and [[Raffles Junior College]], in [[Singapore]].\n\nIn the [[2008 Malaysian general election]], Pua won the parliamentary constituency of [[Petaling Jaya Utara (federal constituency)|Petaling Jaya Utara]] on a DAP ticket. He ran against the incumbent, [[Chew Mei Fun]], then Parliamentary Secretary to the [[Ministry of Women, Family and Community Development]], and Deputy Women Chief of the [[Malaysian Chinese Association]] (MCA).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2008/02/tony-pua-for-parliament.html|title=Tony Pua for Parliament|accessdate=25 February 2008|last=Pua|first=Tony|date=23 February 2008}}</ref> In 2009, Pua was appointed the DAP member of the [[Pakatan Rakyat]] (PR) committee.\n\nPua retained his parliamentary seat in [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]] with a majority of 106,903, the largest majority in Malaysian history.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-election-damansara-parliamentary-seat-sees-biggest-victory-margin|title=Malaysia elections: Damansara parliamentary seat sees biggest victory margin|publisher=[[The Straits Times]]|work=[[Bernama]]|date=10 May 2018|access-date=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nPua attended a secondary school in Singapore on an [[ASEAN]] scholarship from the Singaporean government. He attended [[Raffles Institution]] and Raffles Junior College. He then went to [[Oxford University]], England, where he studied [[philosophy, politics and economics]] at [[Keble College, Oxford|Keble College]] on an [[British American Tobacco|MTC Foundation]] scholarship.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/2/18/focus/16873677&sec=focus |title=From cyber world to arena of politics |accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Tan |first=Joceline |date=18 February 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006021211/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus |archivedate=6 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Early career==\nAfter graduating from Oxford University, Pua worked for Andersen Consulting (now [[Accenture]]) as a consultant. In March 1997, he started [[Cyber Village]], an [[e-business]] consultancy.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121006021211/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus \"From cyber world to arena of politics\"]. (18 February 2007). ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]''</ref> Pua and three friends opened an office in [[Kuala Lumpur]] with four staff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyber-village.net/cvnews_press_theedge.htm |title=Cyber Village does MSC proud |accessdate=15 February 2012 |last=Tan |first=Mary Anne |date=20 July 2001 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211235737/http://www.cyber-village.net/cvnews_press_theedge.htm |archive-date=11 February 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===Bersih 1.0 anniversary vigil arrest===\nOn 9 November 2008, Pua was arrested during a candlelight vigil in [[Petaling Jaya]] to commemorate the first anniversary of the [[Bersih]] street demonstration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2008/11/arrested.html |title=Arrested |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=10 October 2008 }}</ref> Pua was released on police bail on the morning of 10 November 2008 and was later charged for illegal assembly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bersih.org/?p=1548 |title=Candlelight Vigil: All but One Freed |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Ong |first=Andrew |date=10 October 2008 }}</ref>\n\n===Death threat===\nOn 10 August 2010, Pua received a live [[5.56\u00d745mm NATO|5.56mm bullet]] along with a threatening note that were mailed to his constituency service centre. Pua stated that the threat may have been related to his proposal to the [[Selangor]] government to cut [[Bumiputera (Malaysia)|Bumiputera]] discounts for homes and commercial property priced above [[Malaysian ringgit|RM]] 500,000 in the state.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/pua-gets-bullet-in-mail-death-threat/ |title=Pua gets bullet in mail death threat |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Zalkapli |first=Adib |date=10 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100815040705/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/pua-gets-bullet-in-mail-death-threat |archive-date=15 August 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===SYABAS suit===\nOn 28 January 2011, [[Selangor water works|Syarikat Bekalan Air Selangor]] (SYABAS) filed a lawsuit against Pua claiming he had permitted [[Nanyang Siang Pau]]'s Metro edition to publish words defamatory of it. The article quoted him saying the Selangor state government should take over the rights of management of water supply in the state if water concessionaires could not settle their debts. Syabas claimed the report had brought  the company into public scandal and its image had been tarnished. The lawsuit sought an injunction to prevent Pua or his agents from publishing defamatory words against the company, and general damages and cost.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://e.nst.com.my/nst/articles/07mbh/Article |title=Syabas chided over suit |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Surach |first=G |date=11 February 2011 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nPua argued that Syabas, as a public authority performing a public service, had no ''[[locus standi]]'' in making a defamation claim. He also said he had a legal, moral and social duty as an MP and a member of the Selangor government Water Review Panel to publish those words and that the public had a right to know. Pua also filed a counter-suit claiming Syabas' suit was frivolous, vexatious and amounted to an abuse of the court process, which resulted in him suffering losses and unnecessary harassment and expenses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?sec=nation&file=/2011/5/19/nation/20110519174340 |title=PJ Utara MP Tony Pua withdraws bid to dismiss Syabas defamation suit |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=NA |first=NA |date=19 May 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706034144/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2011%2F5%2F19%2Fnation%2F20110519174340&sec=nation |archive-date=6 July 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 6 June 2012, the Malaysian High Court found that SYABAS had proven its case against Pua and ordered him to pay RM200,000 in damages to SYABAS and awarded SYABAS interest at the rate of 4% ''per annum'' from the date of judgment till full payment and also costs. Justice Amelia Tee Hong Geok Abdullah also struck out Pua's counter-claim application and granted SYABAS an injunction to restrain Pua and his agents from further publishing or giving permission to be published \"similar defamatory words\" against SYABAS.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/6/6/nation/20120606164709&sec=nation |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130221035155/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/6/6/nation/20120606164709&sec=nation |url-status=dead |archive-date=21 February 2013 |title=Tony Pua to pay Syabas RM200,000 over defamation suit |accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=NA |first=NA |date=6 June 2012 }}</ref> Pua later stated on his blog that he maintains \"that the above statement is not defamatory, and will instruct my lawyers to file an appeal in the Court of Appeal\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2012/06/tony-pua-ordered-to-pay-rm200000.html|title=Tony Pua Ordered To Pay RM200,000 Damages to SYABAS|accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=6 June 2012 }}</ref>\n\nOn 7 July 2012, Pua posted on his blog that although an appeal was underway, he was required to pay the amount of RM200,000 to SYABAS by 16 July 2012. [[DAP Malaysia]] subsequently initiated a mass fundraising campaign titled \"RM1 for Water Rights: 100,000 Malaysians Support Tony Pua vs Syabas\" calling for 100,000 Malaysians to donate RM1 each to help Pua pay for the damages to SYABAS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2012/07/100000-malaysians-support-tonypua-vs.html|title=100,000 Malaysians Support TonyPua vs SYABAS|accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=7 July 2012 }}</ref>\n\nHe subsequently won the Court of Appeal case. SYABAS appealed the decision to the [[Federal Court of Malaysia]].{{citation needed|date=May 2019}} In the 2015 Federal Court case ([2015] 6 MLJ 187), Pua won the appeal based on the [[Lucas-Box]] principle by providing his own reasonable meaning to the impugned words.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Publications==\n''The Tiger that Lost its Roar'', a tale of Malaysia's political economy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2011/06/you-are-cordially-invited-to-book.html |title=\"The Tiger that Lost its Roar\" \u2013 Petaling Jaya Book Launch!|accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=3 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]''': P106 [[Petaling Jaya Utara (federal constituency)|Damansara]] (previously Petaling Jaya Utara), Selangor<ref>{{cite web\n  | last =\n  | first =\n  | authorlink =\n  | author2 =\n  | title = Malaysia Decides 2008\n  | website =\n  | publisher = [[The Star (Malaysia)]]\n  | date =\n  | url = http://thestar.com.my/election/\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 3 January 2010}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php|title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]]|accessdate=27 May 2010}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{cite web |url= http://undi.info/# | title = Malaysia General Election  | work =undiinfo Malaysian Election Data |publisher= [[Malaysiakini]] |accessdate= 19 April 2013}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]] (GE11).</ref><ref name=\"PRU13\">{{cite web |url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php |title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]]|language=Malay|accessdate=24 March 2017}}Results only available for the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]].</ref><ref name=\"myundi pru 13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |title=my undi : Kawasan & Calon-Calon PRU13 : Keputusan PRU13 (Archived copy) |website=www.myundi.com.my|accessdate=2014-04-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331000718/http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |archivedate=31 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Utusan PRU 13 results\">{{cite web|url=http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum ke-13|work=[[Utusan Malaysia]]|accessdate=26 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321134049/http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|archive-date=21 March 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"GE14 results\">{{cite web|url=https://keputusan.spr.gov.my/|title=SEMAKAN KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM KE - 14|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=17 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"The Star GE14\">{{cite web|url=https://election.thestar.com.my/|title=The Star Online GE14|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref>\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponents\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic Action Party}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|'''37,851'''\n|'''67.92%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|[[Chew Mei Fun]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|17,879\n|32.08%\n|56,257\n|19,972\n|73.47%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic Action Party}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|'''57,407'''\n|'''81.84%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|[[Chew Hoong Ling]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|12,735\n|18.16%\n|70,727\n|44,672\n|82.82%\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{Party shading/Keadilan}} | \n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''121,283'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''89.00%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|Ho Kwok Xheng ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n|14,380\n|10.55%\n| rowspan=\"2\" |137,639\n| rowspan=\"2\" |106,903\n| rowspan=\"2\" |83.76%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/red}} |\n|{{nowrap|Wong Mun Kheong ([[Parti Rakyat Malaysia|PRM]])}}\n|617\n|0.45%\n|}\n\n==Policies==\n[[File:YB_Tony_Pua_with_the_team_of_Trader_Malaysia,_signed_at_PJ_Startup_Festival.jpg|thumb|YB Pua with the team of Trader Malaysia, signed at PJ Startup Festival]]\n\nIn 2012, Pua suggested that the Bumiputera discount for housing and real estate must be abolished for houses above RM500,000. He disagreed with giving discounts on expensive houses such as those priced at or above RM 1 million.<ref>[http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/bahasa/article/diskaun-bumiputera-pas-selangor-tidak-selesa-syor-tony-pua/ Diskaun Bumiputera: PAS Selangor tidak selesa syor Tony Pua] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120914024455/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/bahasa/article/diskaun-bumiputera-pas-selangor-tidak-selesa-syor-tony-pua |date=14 September 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn one of his statements,  Pua said the government should reduce the number of civil servants.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/2/18/focus/16873677&sec=focus |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070222153347/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus |url-status=dead |archive-date=22 February 2007 |title=From cyber world to arena of politics |accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Tan |first=Joceline |date=18 February 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> His idea was rejected by [[People's Justice Party, Malaysia|PKR]] leader [[Anwar Ibrahim]] as impractical. Pua said he wants to make the government sector become more efficient and less costly.<ref>YUEN MEIKENG and RAHIMY RAHIM . [http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2011/11/10/nation/9870006&sec=nation \"Anwar: No to reducing Civil service\"]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}, Kuala Lumpur, 10 November 2011. Retrieved on 25 February 2013.</ref>\n\nPua was invited by the organizers of the recent startup acceleration program held at [[Dewan Sivik]].<ref>[https://trader.my/entertainment/events/petaling-jaya-city-council-mbpj-is-coming-back-with-their-support-for-the-local-startup-scene-in-pj-this-week PJ Startup Festival 2019]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://trader.my/petaling-jaya-city-council-mbpj-is-coming-back-with-their-support-for-the-local-startup-scene-in-pj-this-week/|title=The second PJ Startup Festival is happening this February 2019|last=Ismail|first=Shafiqah|date=2019-02-19|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Damansara (federal constituency)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Tony Pua}}\n* {{official website|http://www.tonypua.com/}}\n* [http://educationmalaysia.blogspot.com/ EDUCATION IN MALAYSIA], an education-oriented blog written by Tony Pua and Kian Ming Ong.\n\n{{Selangor-FedRep}}\n{{Pakatan Harapan}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pua, Tony}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Raffles Institution alumni]]\n[[Category:Raffles Junior College alumni]]\n[[Category:Democratic Action Party (Malaysia) politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Chaoshanese descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:People from Batu Pahat]]\n[[Category:Whistleblowing in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:People from Johor]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:Malaysian politicians of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Keble College, Oxford]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=May 2019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Pan (surname)|Pua (\u6f58)]]}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Other salutations|Tuan]]\n| name          = Tony Pua\n| native_name   = {{nobold|\u6f58\u4fed\u4f1f}}\n| native_name_lang = zh-my\n| honorific-suffix = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image         = 20110414TonyPuaThursday.jpg\n| caption       = Tony Pua giving a speech in a public rally\n| constituency_MP = {{pseat|Damansara}} (earlier {{pseat|Petaling Jaya Utara}})\n| parliament    = Malaysian\n| term_start    = 8 March 2008\n| term_end      =\n| majority      = 19,972 ([[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]])<br />44,672 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])<br />106,903 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n| predecessor   = [[Chew Mei Fun]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]]\u2013[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor     =\n| birth_name    = Tony Pua Kiam Wee\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1972|08|01|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Batu Pahat]], [[Johor]], [[Malaysia]]<ref>{{in lang|zh}} [http://www.sinchew-i.com/sciWWW/node/1501?tid=19 \u5f9e\u653f\u7406\u5ff5\u7c21\u55ae\u8e0f\u5be6\u2027\u6f58\u5109\u5049\u8981\u5e6b\u52a9\u66f4\u591a\u4eba], 1 June 2008, Sinchew Jitpoh</ref>\n| party         = [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP)\n| otherparty    = [[Pakatan Rakyat]] (PR) (2008-2015)<br />[[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) (2015-present)\n| occupation    = [[Politician]], [[investor]]\n| alma_mater    = [[Keble College, Oxford]]\n| website       = {{URL|tonypua.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Tony Pua Kiam Wee''' ({{zh|t=\u6f58\u5109\u5049|s=\u6f58\u4fed\u4f1f|p=P\u0101n Ji\u01cenw\u011bi}}; born 1 August 1972) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP) currently serving as three-term [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] representing [[Damansara (federal constituency)|Damansara]] and Political Secretary to the [[Minister of Finance (Malaysia)|Minister of Finance]] of [[Malaysia]], [[Lim Guan Eng]]. Pua is the former Malaysian CEO of Cyber Village Sdn Bhd, a SESDAQ ([[Singapore Exchange|SGX]] second board)-listed company. In early 2007, he disposed of all his interests in the company and tendered his resignation to join the DAP in 2008.\n\nPua graduated from [[Keble College, Oxford]] with a degree in [[Philosophy, Politics and Economics]] under a scholarship from the [[British American Tobacco|MTC Foundation]] in 1994. Before that, he received Asean and Shaw Foundation scholarships to pursue his O- and A-Levels in [[Raffles Institution]] and [[Raffles Junior College]], in [[Singapore]].\n\nIn the [[2008 Malaysian general election]], Pua won the parliamentary constituency of [[Petaling Jaya Utara (federal constituency)|Petaling Jaya Utara]] on a DAP ticket. He ran against the incumbent, [[Chew Mei Fun]], then Parliamentary Secretary to the [[Ministry of Women, Family and Community Development]], and Deputy Women Chief of the [[Malaysian Chinese Association]] (MCA).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2008/02/tony-pua-for-parliament.html|title=Tony Pua for Parliament|accessdate=25 February 2008|last=Pua|first=Tony|date=23 February 2008}}</ref> In 2009, Pua was appointed the DAP member of the [[Pakatan Rakyat]] (PR) committee.\n\nPua retained his parliamentary seat in [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 general election]] with a majority of 106,903, the largest majority in Malaysian history.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-election-damansara-parliamentary-seat-sees-biggest-victory-margin|title=Malaysia elections: Damansara parliamentary seat sees biggest victory margin|publisher=[[The Straits Times]]|work=[[Bernama]]|date=10 May 2018|access-date=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nPua attended a secondary school in Singapore on an [[ASEAN]] scholarship from the Singaporean government. He attended [[Raffles Institution]] and Raffles Junior College. He then went to [[Oxford University]], England, where he studied [[philosophy, politics and economics]] at [[Keble College, Oxford|Keble College]] on an [[British American Tobacco|MTC Foundation]] scholarship.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/2/18/focus/16873677&sec=focus |title=From cyber world to arena of politics |accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Tan |first=Joceline |date=18 February 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006021211/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus |archivedate=6 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Early career==\nAfter graduating from Oxford University, Pua worked for Andersen Consulting (now [[Accenture]]) as a consultant. In March 1997, he started [[Cyber Village]], an [[e-business]] consultancy.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121006021211/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus \"From cyber world to arena of politics\"]. (18 February 2007). ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]''</ref> Pua and three friends opened an office in [[Kuala Lumpur]] with four staff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyber-village.net/cvnews_press_theedge.htm |title=Cyber Village does MSC proud |accessdate=15 February 2012 |last=Tan |first=Mary Anne |date=20 July 2001 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211235737/http://www.cyber-village.net/cvnews_press_theedge.htm |archive-date=11 February 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===Bersih 1.0 anniversary vigil arrest===\nOn 9 November 2008, Pua was arrested during a candlelight vigil in [[Petaling Jaya]] to commemorate the first anniversary of the [[Bersih]] street demonstration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2008/11/arrested.html |title=Arrested |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=10 October 2008 }}</ref> Pua was released on police bail on the morning of 10 November 2008 and was later charged for illegal assembly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bersih.org/?p=1548 |title=Candlelight Vigil: All but One Freed |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Ong |first=Andrew |date=10 October 2008 }}</ref>\n\n===Death threat===\nOn 10 August 2010, Pua received a live [[5.56\u00d745mm NATO|5.56mm bullet]] along with a threatening note that were mailed to his constituency service centre. Pua stated that the threat may have been related to his proposal to the [[Selangor]] government to cut [[Bumiputera (Malaysia)|Bumiputera]] discounts for homes and commercial property priced above [[Malaysian ringgit|RM]] 500,000 in the state.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/pua-gets-bullet-in-mail-death-threat/ |title=Pua gets bullet in mail death threat |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Zalkapli |first=Adib |date=10 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100815040705/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/pua-gets-bullet-in-mail-death-threat |archive-date=15 August 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===SYABAS suit===\nOn 28 January 2011, [[Selangor water works|Syarikat Bekalan Air Selangor]] (SYABAS) filed a lawsuit against Pua claiming he had permitted [[Nanyang Siang Pau]]'s Metro edition to publish words defamatory of it. The article quoted him saying the Selangor state government should take over the rights of management of water supply in the state if water concessionaires could not settle their debts. Syabas claimed the report had brought  the company into public scandal and its image had been tarnished. The lawsuit sought an injunction to prevent Pua or his agents from publishing defamatory words against the company, and general damages and cost.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://e.nst.com.my/nst/articles/07mbh/Article |title=Syabas chided over suit |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=Surach |first=G |date=11 February 2011 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nPua argued that Syabas, as a public authority performing a public service, had no ''[[locus standi]]'' in making a defamation claim. He also said he had a legal, moral and social duty as an MP and a member of the Selangor government Water Review Panel to publish those words and that the public had a right to know. Pua also filed a counter-suit claiming Syabas' suit was frivolous, vexatious and amounted to an abuse of the court process, which resulted in him suffering losses and unnecessary harassment and expenses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?sec=nation&file=/2011/5/19/nation/20110519174340 |title=PJ Utara MP Tony Pua withdraws bid to dismiss Syabas defamation suit |accessdate=2 February 2012 |last=NA |first=NA |date=19 May 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706034144/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2011%2F5%2F19%2Fnation%2F20110519174340&sec=nation |archive-date=6 July 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn 6 June 2012, the Malaysian High Court found that SYABAS had proven its case against Pua and ordered him to pay RM200,000 in damages to SYABAS and awarded SYABAS interest at the rate of 4% ''per annum'' from the date of judgment till full payment and also costs. Justice Amelia Tee Hong Geok Abdullah also struck out Pua's counter-claim application and granted SYABAS an injunction to restrain Pua and his agents from further publishing or giving permission to be published \"similar defamatory words\" against SYABAS.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/6/6/nation/20120606164709&sec=nation |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130221035155/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/6/6/nation/20120606164709&sec=nation |url-status=dead |archive-date=21 February 2013 |title=Tony Pua to pay Syabas RM200,000 over defamation suit |accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=NA |first=NA |date=6 June 2012 }}</ref> Pua later stated on his blog that he maintains \"that the above statement is not defamatory, and will instruct my lawyers to file an appeal in the Court of Appeal\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2012/06/tony-pua-ordered-to-pay-rm200000.html|title=Tony Pua Ordered To Pay RM200,000 Damages to SYABAS|accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=6 June 2012 }}</ref>\n\nOn 7 July 2012, Pua posted on his blog that although an appeal was underway, he was required to pay the amount of RM200,000 to SYABAS by 16 July 2012. [[DAP Malaysia]] subsequently initiated a mass fundraising campaign titled \"RM1 for Water Rights: 100,000 Malaysians Support Tony Pua vs Syabas\" calling for 100,000 Malaysians to donate RM1 each to help Pua pay for the damages to SYABAS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2012/07/100000-malaysians-support-tonypua-vs.html|title=100,000 Malaysians Support TonyPua vs SYABAS|accessdate=20 July 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=7 July 2012 }}</ref>\n\nHe subsequently won the Court of Appeal case. SYABAS appealed the decision to the [[Federal Court of Malaysia]].{{citation needed|date=May 2019}} In the 2015 Federal Court case ([2015] 6 MLJ 187), Pua won the appeal based on the [[Lucas-Box]] principle by providing his own reasonable meaning to the impugned words.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Publications==\n''The Tiger that Lost its Roar'', a tale of Malaysia's political economy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tonypua.blogspot.com/2011/06/you-are-cordially-invited-to-book.html |title=\"The Tiger that Lost its Roar\" \u2013 Petaling Jaya Book Launch!|accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Pua |first=Tony |date=3 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]''': P106 [[Petaling Jaya Utara (federal constituency)|Damansara]] (previously Petaling Jaya Utara), Selangor<ref>{{cite web\n  | last =\n  | first =\n  | authorlink =\n  | author2 =\n  | title = Malaysia Decides 2008\n  | website =\n  | publisher = [[The Star (Malaysia)]]\n  | date =\n  | url = http://thestar.com.my/election/\n  | doi =\n  | accessdate = 3 January 2010}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php|title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]]|accessdate=27 May 2010}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{cite web |url= http://undi.info/# | title = Malaysia General Election  | work =undiinfo Malaysian Election Data |publisher= [[Malaysiakini]] |accessdate= 19 April 2013}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]] (GE11).</ref><ref name=\"PRU13\">{{cite web |url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php |title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]]|language=Malay|accessdate=24 March 2017}}Results only available for the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]].</ref><ref name=\"myundi pru 13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |title=my undi : Kawasan & Calon-Calon PRU13 : Keputusan PRU13 (Archived copy) |website=www.myundi.com.my|accessdate=2014-04-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331000718/http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |archivedate=31 March 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Utusan PRU 13 results\">{{cite web|url=http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum ke-13|work=[[Utusan Malaysia]]|accessdate=26 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321134049/http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|archive-date=21 March 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"GE14 results\">{{cite web|url=https://keputusan.spr.gov.my/|title=SEMAKAN KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM KE - 14|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=17 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"The Star GE14\">{{cite web|url=https://election.thestar.com.my/|title=The Star Online GE14|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref>\n!|Year\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponents\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic Action Party}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|'''37,851'''\n|'''67.92%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|[[Chew Mei Fun]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|17,879\n|32.08%\n|56,257\n|19,972\n|73.47%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic Action Party}} |\n|{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|'''57,407'''\n|'''81.84%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|[[Chew Hoong Ling]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|12,735\n|18.16%\n|70,727\n|44,672\n|82.82%\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{Party shading/Keadilan}} | \n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{nowrap|'''Tony Pua'''}} ([[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|'''DAP''']])\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''121,283'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''89.00%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|Ho Kwok Xheng ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n|14,380\n|10.55%\n| rowspan=\"2\" |137,639\n| rowspan=\"2\" |106,903\n| rowspan=\"2\" |83.76%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/red}} |\n|{{nowrap|Wong Mun Kheong ([[Parti Rakyat Malaysia|PRM]])}}\n|617\n|0.45%\n|}\n\n==Policies==\n[[File:YB_Tony_Pua_with_the_team_of_Trader_Malaysia,_signed_at_PJ_Startup_Festival.jpg|thumb|YB Pua with the team of Trader Malaysia, signed at PJ Startup Festival]]\n\nIn 2012, Pua suggested that the Bumiputera discount for housing and real estate must be abolished for houses above RM500,000. He disagreed with giving discounts on expensive houses such as those priced at or above RM 1 million.<ref>[http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/bahasa/article/diskaun-bumiputera-pas-selangor-tidak-selesa-syor-tony-pua/ Diskaun Bumiputera: PAS Selangor tidak selesa syor Tony Pua] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120914024455/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/bahasa/article/diskaun-bumiputera-pas-selangor-tidak-selesa-syor-tony-pua |date=14 September 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn one of his statements,  Pua said the government should reduce the number of civil servants.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/2/18/focus/16873677&sec=focus |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070222153347/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F18%2Ffocus%2F16873677&sec=focus |url-status=dead |archive-date=22 February 2007 |title=From cyber world to arena of politics |accessdate=31 January 2012 |last=Tan |first=Joceline |date=18 February 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> His idea was rejected by [[People's Justice Party, Malaysia|PKR]] leader [[Anwar Ibrahim]] as impractical. Pua said he wants to make the government sector become more efficient and less costly.<ref>YUEN MEIKENG and RAHIMY RAHIM . [http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2011/11/10/nation/9870006&sec=nation \"Anwar: No to reducing Civil service\"]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}, Kuala Lumpur, 10 November 2011. Retrieved on 25 February 2013.</ref>\n\nPua was invited by the organizers of the recent startup acceleration program held at [[Dewan Sivik]].<ref>[https://trader.my/entertainment/events/petaling-jaya-city-council-mbpj-is-coming-back-with-their-support-for-the-local-startup-scene-in-pj-this-week PJ Startup Festival 2019]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://trader.my/petaling-jaya-city-council-mbpj-is-coming-back-with-their-support-for-the-local-startup-scene-in-pj-this-week/|title=The second PJ Startup Festival is happening this February 2019|last=Ismail|first=Shafiqah|date=2019-02-19|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Damansara (federal constituency)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Tony Pua}}\n* {{official website|http://www.tonypua.com/}}\n* [http://educationmalaysia.blogspot.com/ EDUCATION IN MALAYSIA], an education-oriented blog written by Tony Pua and Kian Ming Ong.\n\n{{Selangor-FedRep}}\n{{Pakatan Harapan}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pua, Tony}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Raffles Institution alumni]]\n[[Category:Raffles Junior College alumni]]\n[[Category:Democratic Action Party (Malaysia) politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Chaoshanese descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:People from Batu Pahat]]\n[[Category:Whistleblowing in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:People from Johor]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:Malaysian politicians of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Keble College, Oxford]]\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:duplicate categorization; already in subcat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Pua"}
{"title_page": "List of contemporary ethnic groups", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article about ethnicities}}\n{{more citations needed|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2012}}<!-- [[WP:NOETHNICGALLERIES]] -->The following is a '''list of contemporary ethnic groups'''. There has been constant debate over the classification of [[ethnic group]]s. Membership of an ethnic group tends to be associated with shared [[ancestry]], [[history]], [[homeland]], [[language|language or dialect]] and [[cultural heritage]]; where the term \"[[culture]]\" specifically includes aspects such as [[religion]], [[mythology]] and [[ritual]], [[cuisine]], [[national dress|dressing (clothing) style]], and other factors.\n\nBy the nature of the concept, ethnic groups tend to be divided into subgroups, which may themselves be or not be identified as independent ethnic groups depending on the source consulted.\n\n==Ethnic groups==\n{{See also|List of languages by number of native speakers}}\nThe groups commonly identified as \"ethnic groups\" (as opposed to [[ethno-linguistic]] phyla, national groups, [[racial group]]s or similar). Smaller groups (i.e. less than 100,000) are often [[List of indigenous peoples|indigenous peoples]] and are not listed.\n\n{{Dynamic list}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"100%\"\n! style=\"width:8%\"  | Name\n! style=\"width:25%\" |[[Native language]] (primary language)\n! style=\"width:12%\" | Primary [[homeland]]\n! style=\"width:10%\" data-sort-type=\"number\" | Population (estimate)\n! style=\"width:25%\" | Subgroups\n! style=\"width:20%\" | Majority (plurality) religion and sect\n|-\n| [[Abazins]]\n| [[Northwest Caucasian languages]] \u2192 [[Abazgi]] \u2192 [[Abaza language|Abaza]]\n| [[Abazinia]] ([[Russia]])\n| 0.1 million\n| significant populations in [[Turkey]], [[Egypt]] and [[Ukraine]] \n| [[Islam]] \u2192 [[Sunni]]\n|-\n| [[Abkhazians]] \n| [[Northwest Caucasian languages|Northwest Caucasian]] \u2192 [[Abazgi languages|Abazgi]] \u2192 [[Abkhaz language|Abkhaz]]\n| [[Abkhazia]]<ref name=\"Circassian genocide\" group=\"note\">Following the [[Caucasian War]], the majority of Circassians and Abkhazians [[Circassian genocide|were deported]] to Turkey.</ref>\n| 0.2 million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/abk|title=Abkhaz|website=[[Ethnologue]]|accessdate=24 November 2018}} Total Abkhaz users in all countries.</ref>\n|\n| [[Christianity]] \u2192 [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]]\n|-\n| [[Acehnese people|Acehnese]] \n| [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] \u2192 [[Chamic languages|Chamic]] \u2192 [[Acehnese language|Acehnese]]\n| [[Aceh]] ([[Indonesia]])\n| 4.1 million<ref name=\"Indonesia\">{{cite book|publisher=[[Statistics Indonesia]]|title=Kewarganegaraan, Suku Bangsa, Agama dan Bahasa Sehari-hari Penduduk Indonesia Hasil Sensus Penduduk 2010|year=2011|isbn=978-979-064-417-5|url=http://sp2010.bps.go.id/files/ebook/kewarganegaraan%20penduduk%20indonesia/index.html|access-date=24 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710134114/http://sp2010.bps.go.id/files/ebook/kewarganegaraan%20penduduk%20indonesia/index.html|archive-date=10 July 2017|url-status=dead}} Indonesian population only.</ref>\n| [[Aneuk Jamee people|Aneuk Jamee]]\n| [[Islam]] \u2192 [[Sunni Islam]]\n|-\n| [[Acholi people|Acholi]] \n| [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan]] \u2192 [[Nilotic languages|Nilotic]] \u2192 [[Luo languages|Luo]] \u2192 [[Acholi language|Acholi]] \n| [[Northern Region, Uganda|Acholiland]] ([[Uganda]], [[South Sudan]])\n| 1 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/Acholi|title=Acholi|website=[[Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica]]|accessdate=8 March 2019}}</ref>\n|\n| [[Christianity]]\n|-\n| [[Afemai people|Afemai]]\n| [[Niger\u2013Congo languages|Niger\u2013Congo]] \u2192 [[Edoid languages|Edoid]] \u2192 [[Afenmai language|Afenmai]]\n| [[Edo State]] ([[Nigeria]])\n| 0.5 million{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n| \n| [[