 '''Mansor bin Othman''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0645\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u062b\u0645\u0627\u0646) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|BERSATU]]. He is currently the [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] for [[Nibong Tebal]]. He was also the former Penang Deputy Chief Minister I.<ref>[http://www.utusan.com.my/utusan/info.asp?y=2009&dt=0603&pub=utusan_malaysia&sec=Terkini&pg=bt_06.htm&arc=hive \"Mansor angkat sumpah sebagai TKM1 Pulau Pinang\", Utusan Malaysia. 3 Jun 2009.]</ref>\n\nOn 4 December 2018, Mansor was elected chair of the [[Defence and Home Affairs Select Committee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/454684|publisher=[[Malaysiakini]]|accessdate=26 April 2019|title=Six new select committees announced, Anwar heads reforms caucus|date=4 December 2018}}</ref> He was succeeded by [[Nik Nazmi Nik Ahmad]] as chair on 4 December 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/therealmariachin/photos/pcb.3533478726669927/3533443496673450/?type=3&theater|accessdate=8 December 2019|date=4 December 2019|website=facebook.com|last=Abdullah|first=Maria Chin|title=Maria Chin Abdullah}}</ref>\n\n== Political career ==\nHe was also chairman of PKR Penang liaison committee. He served [[Anwar Ibrahim]] as political secretary after leaving his service as senior lecturer at [[University of Science Malaysia]]. He was picked by PKR to contest the [[Penang State Legislative Assembly]] seat of {{nseat|Penanti}} in the [[2009 Penanti by-election|2009 by-election]] and won. In the [[2013 Malaysian general election]], he was nominated to contest the parliamentary seat of {{pseat|Nibong Tebal}} and won. He was re-elected in the [[2018 Malaysian general election]].\n\n== Health issue ==\nOn {{date|2019-10-21}}, Othman collapsed while debating the 2020 Malaysian federal budget, later revealed to be the result of suffering from a [[reflex syncope]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2019/10/21/nibong-tebal-mp-collapses-in-dewan-rakyat|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)]]|title=Nibong Tebal MP collapses in Dewan Rakyat (updated)|date=21 October 2019|first1=Martin|last1=Carvalho|first2=Hemananthani|last2=Sivanandam|first3=Rahimy|last3=Rahim|first4=Tarrence|last4=Tan|accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/496769|publisher=Berita Harian|title=Nibong Tebal MP recovering after mid-speech collapse in Parliament|date=21 October 2019|accessdate=23 October 2019|first=Geraldine|last=Tong}}</ref> He was caught by [[Subang (federal constituency)|Subang]] MP [[Wong Chen]] and [[Ledang (federal constituency)|Ledang]] MP [[Syed Ibrahim Syed Noh]] before being attended to by [[Bandar Kuching (federal constituency)|Bandar Kuching]] MP [[Kelvin Yii Lee Wuen]], who is also a doctor, and later discharged from hospital after his condition stabilised.<ref>{{cite web|date=21 October 2019|accessdate=23 October 2019|url=https://www.bharian.com.my/berita/nasional/2019/10/620056/ahli-parlimen-nibong-tebal-stabil-tpm|publisher=[[Berita Harian]]|language=Malay|title=Ahli Parlimen Nibong Tebal stabil - TPM|first=Ahmad Suhael|last=Adnan}}</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Penang State Legislative Assembly]]'''\n!|Year\n!|Constituency\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponent(s)\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[2009 Penanti by-election|2009]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" |'''N12 [[Penanti (state constituency)|Penanti]], P44 Permatang Pauh'''\n|rowspan=3 {{Party shading/Keadilan}} |\n|rowspan=3|'''Mansor Othman''' ([[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|'''PKR''']])\n|rowspan=3 |'''6,052'''\n|rowspan=3 |'''85.20%'''\n| {{Party shading/Independent}} |\n|Nai-Khan Ari ([[Independent politician|IND]])\n|494\n|6.90%\n|rowspan=3 align=\"right\"|7,100\t\n|rowspan=3 align=\"right\"|5558\