ND]])\n| successor4 =\n\n| assembly5 = Penang State Legislative\n| constituency_AM5 = [[Penanti (state constituency)|Penanti]]\n| term_start5 = 3 June 2009\n| term_end5 = 5 May 2013\n| majority5 = 5,558 ([[2009 Penanti by-election|2009]])\n| predecessor5 = Mohammad Fairus Khairuddin ([[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|PKR]]\u2013[[Pakatan Rakyat|PR]])\n| successor5 = Norlela Ariffin ([[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|PKR]]\u2013[[Pakatan Rakyat|PR]])\n| governor5 = [[Abdul Rahman Abbas]]\n\n| office1 = Deputy Chief Minister I of Penang\n| term_start1 = 3 June 2009\n| term_end1 = 8 May 2013\n| predecessor1 = Mohammad Fairus Khairuddin \n| successor1 = [[Mohd Rashid Hasnon]]\n| constituency1 = [[Penanti (state constituency)|Penanti]]\n| 1blankname1 = Chief Minister\n| 1namedata1 = [[Lim Guan Eng]]\n| governor1 = [[Abdul Rahman Abbas]]\n|office2=[[Penang State Executive Council]]lor for Religious Affairs, Entrepreneur and Co-operatives Development, Information and Community Relations\n| term_start2         = 3 June 2009\n| term_end2           = 8 May 2018\n| governor2          = [[Abdul Rahman Abbas]] \n| 1blankname2         = Chief Minister\n| 1namedata2          = [[Lim Guan Eng]]\n| predecessor2        = Mohammad Fairus Khairuddin \n| successor2          = Abdul Malik Kassim (Religious Affairs) <br/>   [[Mohd Rashid Hasnon]] (Entrepreneur and Co-operatives Development, Community Relations) <br/>   [[Lim Guan Eng]] (Information)\n| office = [[Minister of Education (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Higher Education]]\n| term_end = \n| term_start = 10 March 2020\n| primeminister = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| minister = [[Noraini Ahmad]]\n| constituency = [[Nibong Tebal (federal constituency)|Nibong Tebal]]\n| monarch = [[Abdullah of Pahang|Abdullah]]\n| predecessor = [[Teo Nie Ching]] {{small|as Deputy Minister of Education}}\n| successor = \n| office3 = Chair of the [[Defence and Home Affairs Select Committee]]\n| 1blankname3         = Speaker of House\n| 1namedata3          = [[Mohamad Ariff Md Yusof]]\n| predecessor3 = ''Office established''\n| successor3 = [[Nik Nazmi Nik Ahmad]]\n| term_start3 = 4 December 2018\n| term_end3 = 3 December 2019\n| constituency3 = [[Nibong Tebal (federal constituency)|Nibong Tebal]]\n\n| citizenship = [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]]\n| party = [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] {{small|(2008-2020)}} <br/> [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|BERSATU]] {{small|(2020-present)}}\n| otherparty = [[Pakatan Rakyat]] {{small|(2008-2015)}}<br />[[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) {{small|(2015-2020)}}\n| occupation = [[Politician]]\n| profession = [[Lecturer]]\n| relations = \n| nationality = {{MAS}}\n| spouse = Aishah Binti Zainul\n| children = 3\n| alma_mater = [[University of Science Malaysia]]<br/>[[University of Yale]] \n| website = {{URL|http://mansorothman.com/}}\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n[[Associate Professor|Assoc. Prof.]] [[Malay titles#State titles|Dato']] [[Doctor (title)|Dr.]] '''Mansor bin Othman''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0645\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u062b\u0645\u0627\u0646) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician from the [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|BERSATU]]. He is currently the [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] for [[Nibong Tebal]]. He was also the former Penang Deputy Chief Minister I.<ref>[http://www.utusan.com.my/utusan/info.asp?y=2009&dt=0603&pub=utusan_malaysia&sec=Terkini&pg=bt_06.htm&arc=hive \"Mansor angkat sumpah sebagai TKM1 Pulau Pinang\", Utusan Malaysia. 3 Jun 2009.]</ref>\n\nOn 4 December 2018, Mansor was elected chair of the [[Defence and Home Affairs Select Committee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/454684|publisher=[[Malaysiakini]]|accessdate=26 April 2019|title=Six new select committees announced, Anwar heads reforms caucus|date=4 December 2018}}</ref> He was succeeded by [[Nik Nazmi Nik Ahmad]] as chair on 4 December 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/therealmariachin/photos/pcb.3533478726669927/3533443496673450/?type=3&theater|accessdate=8 December 2019|date=4 December 2019|website=facebook.com|last=Abdullah|first=Maria Chin|title=Maria Chin Abdullah}}</ref>\n\n== Political career ==\nHe was also chairman of PKR Penang liaison committee. He served [[Anwar Ibrahim]] as political secretary after leaving his service as senior lecturer at [[University of Science Malaysia]]. He was picked by PKR to contest the [[Penang State Legislative Assembly]] seat of {{nseat|Penanti}} in the [[2009 Penanti by-election|2009 by-election]] and won. In the [[2013 Malaysian general election]], he was nominated to contest the parliamentary seat of {{pseat|Nibong Tebal}} and won. He was re-elected in the [[2018 Malaysian general election]].\n\n== Health issue ==\nOn {{date|2019-10-21}}, Othman collapsed while debating the 2020 Malaysian federal budget, later revealed to be the result of suffering from a [[reflex syncope]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2019/10/21/nibong-tebal-mp-collapses-in-dewan-rakyat|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)]]|title=Nibong Tebal MP collapses in Dewan Rakyat (updated)|date=21 October 2019|first1=Martin|last1=Carvalho|first2=Hemananthani|last2=Sivanandam|first3=Rahimy|last3=Rahim|first4=Tarrence|last4=Tan|accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/496769|publisher=Berita Harian|title=Nibong Tebal MP recovering after mid-speech collapse in Parliament|date=21 October 2019|accessdate=23 October 2019|first=Geraldine|last=Tong}}</ref> He was caught by [[Subang (federal constituency)|Subang]] MP [[Wong Chen]] and [[Ledang (federal constituency)|Ledang]] MP [[Syed Ibrahim Syed Noh]] before being attended to by [[Bandar Kuching (federal constituency)|Bandar Kuching]] MP [[Kelvin Yii Lee Wuen]], who is also a doctor, and later discharged from hospital after his condition stabilised.<ref>{{cite web|date=21 October 2019|accessdate=23 October 2019|url=https://www.bharian.com.my/berita/nasional/2019/10/620056/ahli-parlimen-nibong-tebal-stabil-tpm|publisher=[[Berita Harian]]|language=Malay|title=Ahli Parlimen Nibong Tebal stabil - TPM|first=Ahmad Suhael|last=Adnan}}</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Penang State Legislative Assembly]]'''\n!|Year\n!|Constituency\n!colspan=2|\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opponent(s)\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[2009 Penanti by-election|2009]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" |'''N12 [[Penanti (state constituency)|Penanti]], P44 Permatang Pauh'''\n|rowspan=3 {{Party shading/Keadilan}} |\n|rowspan=3|'''Mansor Othman''' ([[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|'''PKR''']])\n|rowspan=3 |'''6,052'''\n|rowspan=3 |'''85.20%'''\n| {{Party shading/Independent}} |\n|Nai-Khan Ari ([[Independent politician|IND]])\n|494\n|6.90%\n|rowspan=3 align=\"right\"|7,100\t\n|rowspan=3 align=\"right\"|5558\n|rowspan=3 align=\"right\"|46.10%\n|-\n| {{Party shading/Independent}} |\n|Aminah Abdullah ([[Independent politician|IND]])\n|392\n|5.50%\n|-\n| {{Party shading/Independent}} |\n|Kamarul Ramizu Idris ([[Independent politician|IND]])\n|56\n|0.70%\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:90%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]'''<ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{cite web |url= http://undi.info/# | title = Malaysia General Election  | work =undiinfo Malaysian Election Data |publisher= [[Malaysiakini]] |accessdate= 19 April 2013}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]] (GE11).</ref><ref name=\"PRU13 results\">{{cite web|url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php|title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref><ref name =\"myundi pru 13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13